[32m+[m[32m## Environment Reference[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThe auth service reads environment from the host-provided plugin service context and falls back to[m
[32m+[m[32m`Deno.env` only for direct service startup. `NETSCRIPT_AUTH_BACKEND` selects one backend; backend-[m
[32m+[m[32mspecific variables are required only when that backend is active.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m| Variable                                    | Backend                | Required                                | Purpose                                                                              |[m
[32m+[m[32m| ------------------------------------------- | ---------------------- | --------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |[m
[32m+[m[32m| `NETSCRIPT_AUTH_BACKEND`                    | all                    | no                                      | Active backend name: `kv-oauth`, `workos`, or `better-auth`. Defaults to `kv-oauth`. |[m
[32m+[m[32m| `NETSCRIPT_AUTH_CLIENT_ID`                  | kv-oauth               | yes for real sign-in                    | OAuth/OIDC client id.                                                                |[m
[32m+[m[32m| `NETSCRIPT_AUTH_CLIENT_SECRET`              | kv-oauth               | provider-dependent                      | OAuth/OIDC client secret when the token endpoint requires one.                       |[m
[32m+[m[32m| `NETSCRIPT_AUTH_ISSUER`                     | kv-oauth               | issuer mode                             | OIDC issuer used for discovery.                                                      |[m
[32m+[m[32m| `NETSCRIPT_AUTH_AUTHORIZATION_ENDPOINT`     | kv-oauth               | static-endpoint mode                    | Authorization endpoint when no issuer is configured.                                 |[m
[32m+[m[32m| `NETSCRIPT_AUTH_TOKEN_ENDPOINT`             | kv-oauth               | static-endpoint mode                    | Token endpoint when no issuer is configured.                                         |[m
[32m+[m[32m| `NETSCRIPT_AUTH_USERINFO_ENDPOINT`          | kv-oauth               | no                                      | Optional userinfo endpoint for providers without OIDC claims.                        |[m
[32m+[m[32m| `NETSCRIPT_AUTH_REDIRECT_URI`               | kv-oauth               | yes for real sign-in                    | Absolute callback URL registered with the provider.                                  |[m
[32m+[m[32m| `NETSCRIPT_AUTH_SCOPES`                     | kv-oauth               | no                                      | Space-delimited provider scopes. Defaults are provider-owned.                        |[m
[32m+[m[32m| `NETSCRIPT_AUTH_COOKIE_NAME`                | kv-oauth               | no                                      | Session cookie name. Defaults to the backend package default.                        |[m
[32m+[m[32m| `NETSCRIPT_AUTH_KV_OAUTH_KEY`               | kv-oauth with KV store | yes                                     | Base64 AES-256 key material, exactly 32 decoded bytes.                               |[m
[32m+[m[32m| `NETSCRIPT_AUTH_ALLOW_INSECURE_REQUESTS`    | kv-oauth               | local dev only                          | Set to `true` only for local HTTP OAuth flows.                                       |[m
[32m+[m[32m| `WORKOS_API_KEY`                            | WorkOS                 | yes                                     | WorkOS API key.                                                                      |[m
[32m+[m[32m| `WORKOS_CLIENT_ID`                          | WorkOS                 | yes                                     | WorkOS application client id.                                                        |[m
[32m+[m[32m| `WORKOS_COOKIE_PASSWORD`                    | WorkOS                 | yes                                     | WorkOS sealed-session cookie password.                                               |[m
[32m+[m[32m| `BETTER_AUTH_SECRET`                        | better-auth            | yes                                     | Secret used by better-auth and the NetScript session-token wrapper.                  |[m
[32m+[m[32m| `DB_PROVIDER`                               | better-auth            | no                                      | Prisma provider hint. Defaults to `postgresql`.                                      |[m
[32m+[m[32m| `PORT`                                      | service                | no                                      | Auth API service port. Defaults to `8094`.                                           |[m
[32m+[m[32m| `NETSCRIPT_PLUGIN_SERVICE_BOOTSTRAP_MODULE` | direct startup         | yes for `deno run services/src/main.ts` | Module that exports `createPluginServiceContext`.                                    |[m
[32m+[m[32m| `DURABLE_STREAMS_URL`                       | streams/server         | no                                      | Durable streams service URL for best-effort projection writes.                       |[m
[32m+[m[32m| `services__streams__http__0`                | streams/server         | no                                      | Aspire service discovery URL for durable streams.                                    |[m
[32m+[m[32m| `VITE_services__streams__http__0`           | streams/server         | no                                      | Browser-build service discovery URL for durable streams.                             |[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m`createInMemoryKvOAuthRegistry()` is the only path that supplies the deterministic auth key used in[m
[32m+[m[32mtests. Production kv-oauth stores must set `NETSCRIPT_AUTH_KV_OAUTH_KEY`.[m
