[32m+[m[32m## Mount Recipe[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mGenerated NetScript apps mount the official plugin through scaffold metadata. Manual local-source[m
[32m+[m[32mapps add the auth plugin to their plugin registry, provide the database and KV resources expected by[m
[32m+[m[32mthe service context, and start the contributed `auth-api` service alongside the app services.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```ts[m
[32m+[m[32mimport { authPlugin } from '@netscript/plugin-auth';[m
[32m+[m[32mimport createAuthService from '@netscript/plugin-auth/services';[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mconst manifest = authPlugin;[m
[32m+[m[32mconst service = await createAuthService(pluginServiceContext);[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mconsole.log(manifest.name, service.addr.port);[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThe auth handlers need the real service request captured by the service middleware. Direct unit[m
[32m+[m[32mtests should pass explicit fixture URLs; production code should not call the interactive handlers[m
[32m+[m[32mwithout the service request context.[m
